This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with action recognition from video data. The use of probabilistic graphical models also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of in-house datasets suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the mention of experimental results suggests that it could also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
